title: New Specialist, map revealed in live-stream video of Black Ops III
text:
Search for: New Specialist, map revealed in live-stream video of Black Ops III Posted on October 9, 2015 in PC News , PlayStation 3 News , PlayStation 4 News , Xbox 360 News , Xbox One News 
Treyarch has released an archive video of their first Black Fridays live-stream event for Call of Duty: Black Ops III. The inaugural stream revealed the ninth Specialist, Firebreak, and a new multiplayer map, Redwood. In addition to the archive, a handful of screenshots were also released to show Redwood in greater detail. Everything is available below to check out. 
Call of Duty: Black Ops III is scheduled to launch on November 6 for PC, PS3, PS4, Xbox 360, and Xbox One. Note: “PS3 and Xbox 360 platform version features and performance may vary compared to other platform versions.” 
–
